HEADWORD: Momentous
<hw>Mo*men"tous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>momentosus</ets> rapid, momentary.]</ety> <def>Of moment or
consequence; very important; weighty; <as>as, a <ex>momentous</ex>
decision; <ex>momentous</ex> affairs.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Mo*men"tous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mo*men"tous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>momentousness</ent>⟦br⟧
